{"id": 123407, "published_time": "2023-04-02T13:53:00+00:00", "expires_time": "2023-04-03T13:53:00+00:00", "created_at": "2023-04-02T12:38:37+00:00", "updated_at": "2023-04-02T13:53:39+00:00", "author": "Steve Reynaud", "product_type": "forecast", "bottom_line": "<p>Human triggered wind slab avalanches continue to occur in the backcountry with multiple close calls reported yesterday.&nbsp; Strong winds today will continue to form unstable slabs of wind-blown snow.&nbsp; Avalanche danger will increase late this afternoon/evening and through tonight as a winter storm enters our region.</p>", "hazard_discussion": "<div class=\"nac-tinymce\" data-v-48c83ac7=\"\">\n<div class=\"nac-tinymce\" data-v-48c83ac7=\"\">\n<ul class=\"nac-html-ul\">\n<li class=\"nac-html-li\">Unstable wind <a class=\"nac-html-a\" href=\"https://avalanche.org/avalanche-encyclopedia/snowpack/slab/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-markjs=\"true\" data-tippy-content=\"A relatively cohesive snowpack layer.\">slabs</a> continue in some ridgetop areas.&nbsp; Many human triggered wind slab avalanches have occurred over the past few days throughout the forecast region.&nbsp; Check out our <a href=\"https://www.sierraavalanchecenter.org/observations\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">observation page</a> or the Media Gallery below for more information.</li>\n<li class=\"nac-html-li\">A large <a class=\"nac-glossary\" href=\"https://avalanche.org/avalanche-encyclopedia/avalanche/avalanche-problems/avalanche-problem-type/cornice-fall/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-markjs=\"true\" data-tippy-content=\"A mass of snow deposited by the wind, often overhanging, and usually near a sharp terrain break such as a ridge. Cornices can break off unexpectedly and should be approached with caution.\">cornice</a> <a class=\"nac-glossary\" href=\"https://avalanche.org/avalanche-encyclopedia/snowpack/snowpack-observations/signs-of-instability-red-flags/collapse-or-whumpf/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-markjs=\"true\" data-tippy-content=\"When the fracture of a lower snow layer causes an upper layer to fall. Also called a whumpf, this is an obvious sign of instability.\">collapse</a> occurred in Ward Canyon on Friday.</li>\n<li class=\"nac-html-li\">Several inches of unconsolidated snow were observed yesterday along the ridgetops, available for transport as wind speeds increase.</li>\n<li class=\"nac-html-li\">Sun crusts have formed on most sun-exposed slopes across nearly all aspects.</li>\n<li class=\"nac-html-li\">Signs of persistent instability on <a class=\"nac-html-a\" href=\"https://avalanche.org/avalanche-encyclopedia/snowpack/weak-layer/storm-snow-weak-layers/graupel-rimed-particles/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-markjs=\"true\" data-tippy-content=\"Heavily rimed new snow, often shaped like little Styrofoam balls.\">graupel</a> and crust <a class=\"nac-html-a\" href=\"https://avalanche.org/avalanche-encyclopedia/snowpack/snow-layer/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-markjs=\"true\" data-tippy-content=\"A snowpack stratum differentiated from others by weather, metamorphism, or other processes.\">layers</a> across NW-N-NE <a class=\"nac-html-a\" href=\"https://avalanche.org/avalanche-encyclopedia/terrain/slope-characteristics/aspect/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-markjs=\"true\" data-tippy-content=\"The compass direction a slope faces (i.e. North, South, East, or West.)\">aspects</a> within the forecast area have become increasingly isolated and difficult to trigger. <a class=\"nac-html-a\" href=\"https://avalanche.org/avalanche-encyclopedia/avalanche/trigger/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-markjs=\"true\" data-tippy-content=\"A disturbance that initiates fracture within the weak layer causing an avalanche. In 90 percent of avalanche accidents, the victim or someone in the victims party triggers the avalanche.\">Triggering</a> an isolated <a class=\"nac-html-a\" href=\"https://avalanche.org/avalanche-encyclopedia/avalanche/avalanche-problems/avalanche-problem-type/persistent-slab/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-markjs=\"true\" data-tippy-content=\"Avalanche problem caused by weak layers buried in the snowpack that can produce avalanches for several days or weeks after a storm.\">persistent slab</a> <a class=\"nac-html-a\" href=\"https://avalanche.org/avalanche-encyclopedia/avalanche/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-markjs=\"true\" data-tippy-content=\"A mass of snow sliding, tumbling, or flowing down an inclined surface.\">avalanche</a> 1.5 to 4+ feet deep in snowpack has become unlikely on a regional scale yet still not impossible.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>", "weather_discussion": null, "announcement": null, "status": "published", "media": [{"id": 1, "url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3060_copy_6428f2997a5cc-large.jpg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3060_copy_6428f2997a5cc-medium.jpg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3060_copy_6428f2997a5cc.jpg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3060_copy_6428f2997a5cc-thumbnail.jpg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(4/1/2023) <p>Skier triggered wind slab avalanche on Hawkins Peak, Woodfords Canyon.</p> Photo: Public"}, {"id": 2, "url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3058_copy_6428f297e8713-large.jpg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3058_copy_6428f297e8713-medium.jpg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3058_copy_6428f297e8713.jpg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3058_copy_6428f297e8713-thumbnail.jpg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(4/1/2023) <p>Skier triggered wind slab avalanche on Hawkins Peak, Woodfords Canyon.&nbsp; </p> Photo: Public"}, {"id": 3, "url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012231-2dc950de-aba1-4f06-89de-b7067fa4ec8f_64297d4c83b85-large.jpeg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012231-2dc950de-aba1-4f06-89de-b7067fa4ec8f_64297d4c83b85-medium.jpeg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012231-2dc950de-aba1-4f06-89de-b7067fa4ec8f_64297d4c83b85.jpeg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012231-2dc950de-aba1-4f06-89de-b7067fa4ec8f_64297d4c83b85-thumbnail.jpeg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(4/1/2023) <p>Human triggered wind slab avalanche on Red Lake Peak, Carson Pass.</p> Photo: Public"}, {"id": 4, "url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012231-6a388c5d-744d-496e-9bfc-9b16c7f1d6b1_64297d4e1acde-large.jpeg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012231-6a388c5d-744d-496e-9bfc-9b16c7f1d6b1_64297d4e1acde-medium.jpeg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012231-6a388c5d-744d-496e-9bfc-9b16c7f1d6b1_64297d4e1acde.jpeg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012231-6a388c5d-744d-496e-9bfc-9b16c7f1d6b1_64297d4e1acde-thumbnail.jpeg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(4/1/2023) <p>Human triggered wind slab avalanche on Red Lake Peak, Carson Pass.</p> Photo: Public"}, {"id": 5, "url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012003-da8395ac-3dcb-4bd0-a01e-096bbb76c9af_6428f2958c2cc-large.jpeg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012003-da8395ac-3dcb-4bd0-a01e-096bbb76c9af_6428f2958c2cc-medium.jpeg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012003-da8395ac-3dcb-4bd0-a01e-096bbb76c9af_6428f2958c2cc.jpeg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304012003-da8395ac-3dcb-4bd0-a01e-096bbb76c9af_6428f2958c2cc-thumbnail.jpeg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(4/1/2023) <p>Snowmobiler triggered wind slab avalanche on Secrets Bowl, Little Truckee Summit.</p> Photo: Public"}, {"id": 6, "url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311609-20230331_132213_64279fd26bf8f-large.jpg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311609-20230331_132213_64279fd26bf8f-medium.jpg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311609-20230331_132213_64279fd26bf8f.jpg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311609-20230331_132213_64279fd26bf8f-thumbnail.jpg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(3/31/2023) <p>Wind slab avalanche snowboarder triggered on north side of Castle Peak, Donner Summit area.</p> Photo: Public"}, {"id": 7, "url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311642-img-4848_64279fd56b38b-large.jpg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311642-img-4848_64279fd56b38b-medium.jpg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311642-img-4848_64279fd56b38b.jpg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311642-img-4848_64279fd56b38b-thumbnail.jpg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(3/31/2023) <p>Large cornice collapse in Ward Canyon.</p> Photo: Public"}, {"id": 8, "url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311642-img-4857_64279fd60405f-large.jpg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311642-img-4857_64279fd60405f-medium.jpg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311642-img-4857_64279fd60405f.jpg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202303311642-img-4857_64279fd60405f-thumbnail.jpg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(3/31/2023) <p>Large cornice collapse in Ward Canyon.</p> Photo: Public"}, {"id": 9, "url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/ws_6426dc8230794-large.jpg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/ws_6426dc8230794-medium.jpg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/ws_6426dc8230794.jpg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/ws_6426dc8230794-thumbnail.jpg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(3/30/2023) <p>Unstable wind slabs failing 4 to 6 inches deep with several inches of snow on the ridgetop still available for drifting. Hidden Peak, West Shore Tahoe area, CA</p> Photo: SAC"}, {"id": 10, "url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/rb_6426dc8229369-large.jpg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/rb_6426dc8229369-medium.jpg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/rb_6426dc8229369.jpg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/rb_6426dc8229369-thumbnail.jpg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(3/30/2023) <p>Roller balls formed around noon in sun exposed terrain, Donner Summit, CA.</p> Photo: SAC"}], "weather_data": {"weather_product_id": 123406}, "json_data": null, "avalanche_center": {"id": "SAC", "name": "Sierra Avalanche Center", "url": "https://www.sierraavalanchecenter.org/", "city": "Truckee", "state": "CA"}, "forecast_avalanche_problems": [{"id": 801582, "forecast_id": 123407, "avalanche_problem_id": 3, "rank": 1, "likelihood": "possible", "discussion": "<p>Multiple reports came in again yesterday of human triggered wind slab avalanches throughout the forecast region.&nbsp; Over the past multiple days, these wind slabs have continued to grow in size with consistent strong to gale force SW winds.&nbsp; These wind slabs have not bonded and gained strength in many areas and are expected to be reactive again today.&nbsp; Some wind slab avalanche reports yesterday had deep crowns with wide propagation- producing size D2+ avalanches.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Avalanche danger will increase late this afternoon or early evening as snow begins to occur in our area with more wind transport expected.&nbsp; With the strength of the wind speeds and the additional snow forecasted, some wind slabs could form in below treeline areas.&nbsp; Use caution while traveling around areas where unstable wind slabs may exist.&nbsp; Areas below ridgelines, slopes below cornices, and areas with blowing snow, will all be likely areas for wind slabs to exist.</p>", "media": {"url": {"large": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3060_copy_6428f2997a5cc-large.jpg", "medium": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3060_copy_6428f2997a5cc-medium.jpg", "original": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3060_copy_6428f2997a5cc.jpg", "thumbnail": "https://avalanche-org-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/202304011908-img_3060_copy_6428f2997a5cc-thumbnail.jpg"}, "type": "image", "title": null, "caption": "(4/1/2023) <p>Skier triggered wind slab avalanche on Hawkins Peak, Woodfords Canyon.</p> Photo: Public"}, "location": ["northwest upper", "northwest middle", "north middle", "north upper", "northeast upper", "northeast middle", "east middle", "east upper", "southeast upper", "southeast middle"], "size": ["1", "2.5"], "name": "Wind Slab", "problem_description": "Wind Slab avalanches are the release of a cohesive layer of snow (a slab) formed by the wind. Wind typically transports snow from the upwind sides of terrain features and deposits snow on the downwind side. Wind slabs are often smooth and rounded and sometimes sound hollow, and can range from soft to hard. Wind slabs that form over a persistent weak layer (surface hoar, depth hoar, or near-surface facets) may be termed Persistent Slabs or may develop into Persistent Slabs.", "icon": "http://api.avalanche.org/img/avalanche_problems/WindSlab.png"}], "danger": [{"lower": 2, "upper": 2, "middle": 2, "valid_day": "current"}, {"lower": 3, "upper": 3, "middle": 3, "valid_day": "tomorrow"}], "forecast_zone": [{"id": 77, "name": "Central Sierra Nevada", "url": "https://www.sierraavalanchecenter.org/forecasts/#/central-sierra-nevada", "state": "CA", "zone_id": "1"}]}